#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:1
msgid "Trainer Duties and Agreement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:3
msgid ""
"As of May 2017, the Trainers group adopted a Trainer Agreement outlining "
"Trainer duties. Only active Trainers are voting members of the Trainer "
"community. An inactive Trainer may re-activate their Trainer status at "
"any time by resuming Trainer activities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:5
msgid "Trainer Agreement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:7
msgid ""
"I agree to follow the Code of Conduct (CoC) in all communications and "
"interactions with The Carpentries community and to promptly report any "
"violations of the CoC that I become aware of."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:9
msgid ""
"I understand that the secondary learning outcomes of workshops are as "
"important as their stated goals. I will:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:10
msgid ""
"Communicate The Carpentries community values to trainees and model that "
"behaviour myself in how I teach"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:11
msgid "Provide a welcoming and supporting environment for trainees"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:12
msgid "Model our “show, don’t tell” policy in instructor training"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:13
msgid ""
"Connect the principles used in The Carpentries workshops with other "
"teaching contexts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:15
msgid ""
"I understand that it is important to keep up to date and in touch with "
"the Trainer community so that my teaching will reflect current practices "
"and curriculum. Therefore, to be an active Trainer, I agree to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:16
msgid "Teach at least two instructor training events per year"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:17
msgid "Host on average four teaching demonstrations per year  (1 per quarter)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:18
msgid ""
"Regularly attend Trainer meetings when possible and read meeting "
"minutes/notes when I am not able to attend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:19
msgid "Read emails sent to the Trainer listserv"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:20
msgid "Keep up-to-date with the instructor training curriculum"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:21
msgid ""
"Teach a curriculum that fulfills all of the current requirements for "
"instructor certification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:22
msgid ""
"Provide feedback to other trainers and Carpentries staff about training "
"events to help continue developing our offerings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/duties_agreement.md:24
msgid ""
"I understand that The Carpentries staff need an accurate understanding of"
" Trainer availability in order to plan instructor training events. If at "
"any point I am no longer able to serve as a Trainer, I will let The "
"Carpentries staff know. I understand that only active Trainers are voting"
" members of the Trainer community, but that I will be able to re-activate"
" my Trainer status at any time by resuming Trainer activities."
msgstr ""

